<TEXT>
two chinese dancers and a member of a 
soviet troupe apparently defected to the united states after 
appearing in a utah folk festival police said tuesday 
the three women two from the peoples republic of china and one 
from the ukraine left their american host families homes at 
separate times but later telephoned the families to inform them they 
had defected and were safe said springville police sgt dave caron 
himself a host for two soviet dancers 
both cases were being handled by the fbi and the us immigration 
and naturalization service and the dancers whereabouts were 
unknown he said 
the chinese women identified as chen li 24 and zhe qian 27 
both from guizhou province in southeast china disappeared friday 
the soviet woman svetlana kirenko 32 of the donetsk region 
just north of the black sea refused to join her troupe which was 
boarding a bus for salt lake international airport early tuesday 
caron said 
early this morning when it was time to go she told the host 
family that she did not intend to return to the soviet union and she 
wanted to defect she refused to get in the car or put her suitcase 
in the car to go where the bus was picking up the dancers he said 
kirenko would not leave the house he said and when the host 
family and other soviet dancers went inside a short time later to 
talk to her they found her gone 
tour organizers were upset but its not like they were angry 
they were concerned caron said they realized the impact of a 
choice like that this lady has basically decided to give up her 
entire life to come to america they were concerned about her 
wellbeing 
they were primarily concerned that the lady made the decision 
on her own and that is really what she wanted to do he added 
the women were among several hundred dancers from various foreign 
countries appearing in the world folk fest in springville about 60 
miles south of here which began aug 12 and ended monday 
springville police turned the matter over to federal authorities 
caron said fbi spokesman tim screen said he could not comment on 
the matter ins administrators whose office was closed tuesday 
night could not be reached 
caron said it wasnt immediately known how the women fled or if 
they had help 
