the result was expected to be finalized thursday when any 
questionable votes could be challenged if the vote stands as 
expected a runoff will be held sept 5 between miss cork and ames 
gibson said 
miss cork who was bidding to succeed her father the late rep 
william n cork favors a womans right to abortion as does ames 
graves opposes abortion 
miss cork said after the election that the national attention 
focused on abortion made the voters here think about it more 
but said she wasnt sure if it played a role in the primary 
ames said the issue was important but said it would probably be 
less of a factor in the runoff because both he and miss cork are 
prochoice he said such issues as realestate taxes uncontrolled 
growth and traffic and drugs would become more important 
graves said his stand on abortion may have cost him votes 
the issue had dominated the campaign transcending the 
environment education taxes and crime the general assembly is 
