northeastern ethiopia sunday through tuesday the quakes registered 
as high as 65 on the richter scale the agency reported tuesday 
the fatalities occurred when landslides overturned four trucks 
and badly damaged a 19mile stretch of highway leading to the red 
sea port of assab the agency said 
the port handles 70 percent of ethiopias trade as well as much 
of the relief food needed by refugees and drought victims in this 
impoverished east african nation ethiopias only oil refinery also 
is at the port 
the agency said six bridges also were destroyed in the earthquake 
assab officials said the landslides killed 250 camels and goats 
and covered many of the water wells in the arid region 
much of the regions seminomadic population had fled the area 
seeking shelter and food from nearby villages the news agency said 
the earthquakes epicenter was described as 320 miles northeast 
of the capital addis ababa between the towns of dubti and serdo 
earthquakes of similar severity hit the same region in 1961 causing 
several buildings to collapse 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph every increase of one number means the ground motion is 
10 times greater a quake of magnitude 65 can cause severe damage 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

