hurricane erin continued its northerly tour of the 
midatlantic wednesday but forecasters gave it little chance of 
approaching land with its 75 mph winds 
at 6 pm edt the hurricanes center was located near 325 north 
latitude and 461 west longitude or about 950 miles southwest of 
the westernmost azores the national hurricane center in suburban 
coral gables reported 
itll start accelerating up toward the northnortheast it 
probably wont develop much more over the next few days said 
meteorologist jesse moore its not expected to affect any land 
area 
the storm moving north at about 7 mph was expected to pick up 
speed thursday storms are fed by warm waters and generally lose 
strength as they head into cooler waters 
the hurricane posed a danger to maritime traffic in the open 
atlantic but ships have been warned to stay away 
erin was spawned off the africa coast became a named storm 
sunday night when sustained winds reached 39 mph and was upgraded to 
a hurricane tuesday morning when a ship sailing near the center 
reported high winds 
there have been seven depressions in the atlantic hurricane 
season running from june 1 to nov 30 erin is the third hurricane 
of the year hurricanes are formed when sustained winds hit 74 mph 
