<TEXT>
for anyone who played with toy tonka trucks and dreamed about 
what they would be like on real roads there is an answer the 1990 
toyota 4runner 4door 4wd with v6 engine 
this new 4runner like an obliging toy will bound hills with ease 
slink down inclines in a stable admiring way and capably blaze 
trails then as many popular toys do it will change personalities 
for the ride home on regular roads the 4runner 4wd switches from 
fourwheeldrive to twowheelrive with the touch of a gear shifter 
here the 3liter electronic fuelinjected v6 engine is truly 
appreciated providing smooth good acceleration in the test 
vehicle which also was equipped with a fourspeed automatic 
transmission and like all longrunning toys the 4runner has a 
reputation for durability 
for the last three years the 4runner has finished first in its 
class in jd power amp associates compact truck satisfaction index 
in the most recent survey in 1988 toyota 4runner owners said their 
vehicle had few fitandfinish problems at delivery and they ranked 
reliability high 
the 1990 model is toyotas first fourdoor version of the 
4runner which has been sold in this country as a twodoor since 
late 1983 but more than just two doors have been added 
the new 4runner marks the second generation of the 4runner and 
features a more rounded exterior an upscale interior and 
shiftonthefly fourwheeldrive that can be engaged in speeds of 
up to 50 mph it appears to be a new generation of promise 
the test vehicle was capable where it counted on all kinds of 
roads over many kinds of bumps and holes and at different speeds 
a new suspension including a fourlink coil spring system in the 
rear gave a stable feel to the handling though toyota warned in 
its owners manual that the 4runner like all sport utility 
vehicles maneuvers differently than a regular car and must be 
driven carefully 
the 4runner had good ground clearance 10 inches to get over 
rocks and stumps when offroading it came in handy too when 
someone left a truck tire in the middle of a highway lane during the 
test drive 
of course the 4runners high profile the door handles were 
above my waist also made for some interesting maneuvering of my 
own as i scampered inside thankfully getting out was easier just 
sliding sliding sliding down 
superb described the fit and finish inside and out and toyota 
wants to make sure the vehicle stays in top form the automaker uses 
greater amounts of galvanized steel on the new model a coated 
frame chip resistant paint specially shaped rocker panels and 
special wax coat on hinges to protect against the elements 
inside the optional cloth sport seats in front the decent 
legroom in back and generally pleasant surroundings made the outside 
elements seem distant 
even the inside roof was clothcovered in the test 4runner 
the rear cargo area behind the split rear seat was nicely 
carpeted with attention given to carpeting the rounded tops of the 
wheel wells back there it was a spacious cargo area even with the 
rear seats not folded down 
the rear window of the 4runner slides down electrically with the 
turn of the key in the rear door or from the inside with the touch 
of a button on the center console next to the driver theres also a 
button on the console to lock the window so it cant be 
accidentally opened 
the rear door folds down outward is carpeted and makes a nice 
shelf for tailgating at football games 
but the 4runner test vehicle wasnt cheap base price for the 
1990 4runner 4door 4wd sr5 v6 the official name of the tester 
was more than 19000 including automatic transmission with 
options and delivery charge it totaled more than 22000 and 
thats without power windows power locks and cassette player 
in contrast ford said its large twodoor bronco 
fourwheeldrive sport utility vehicle with sixcylinder engine 
threespeed automatic transmission air conditioning and many other 
options on the 4runner would total about 18000 
you can find a lowerpriced 4runner with a manual transmission 
and a fourcylinder engine with a base price of more than 15400 
toyota expects the new 4runner to attract a different crowd than 
the previous one prior buyers were predominantly male with median 
age of 32 sixtynine percent were married 44 percent were college 
graduates and the average income was 44000 
company spokesman mike michaels said toyota expects the number of 
women buyers to increase with the new model because it will be a 
more attractive package for adventurous families michaels also said 
toyota expects to attract an older higherincome crowd 
sales of 4runners last year totaled 28000 and had been tapering 
downward for a couple years michaels said but he added that toyota 
hopes to double even triple sales once the new model takes hold 
consumer report magazine did not have a listing for owner reports 
on the 4runner 
</TEXT>
