cbs won us television rights to the 1994 winter 
olympics at lillehammer norway with a bid of 300 million the 
associated press learned wednesday 
cbs last year won rights to the 1992 winter olympics at 
albertville france for 243 million nbc won the rights to the 
1992 summer olympics at barcelona spain for 401 million 
the top price for a winter olympics was the 309 million abc paid 
for the 1988 games at calgary alberta 
the bidding for rights to the lillehammer games had been 
scheduled for sept 7 a network source familiar with the 
negotiations said abc had told the olympic organizers that it did 
not intend to bid 
the source said that the organizers told nbc that cbs had 
previously guaranteed a minimum bid of 290 million cbs sports 
president neal pilson traveled to toronto on tuesday to finalize the 
deal with international olympic committee vice president richard 
pound after nbc apparently said it would not match cbs minimum bid 
cbs scheduled a news conference for late wednesday in new york to 
make the announcement there was no immediate reaction from nbc or 
abc 
